Submit review findings using `artifact_type="issues"`.

The `issues` artifact is a markdown document (grammar: `.agent/artifact-formats/issues.md`):
`---` frontmatter with `type: issues` and `status: no_issues|issues_found`, then:
- `## Summary` — exactly one item: a one-sentence summary of the review.
- `## Issues` — one item per finding, text formatted `path | severity | summary` (severity: `high`, `medium`, or `low`).
- `## What Came Up Short` — one item per defect, regression, missing requirement, unsafe change, or verification gap.
- `## How To Fix` — one item per gap: ordered, concrete remediation the fixer can execute directly (exact files, changes, checks to run, expected outcomes).

Rules:
- When `status` is `no_issues`, omit `## Issues`, `## What Came Up Short`, and `## How To Fix` (or leave them empty).
- When `status` is `issues_found`, all three sections must be non-empty.
- Cite concrete evidence in every gap: file paths, failing tests, missing checks, or behavior mismatches. No vague summaries.

{% set issues_example %}
---
type: issues
status: no_issues
---

## Summary
- [SUM-1] The implementation is correct and verification passed.
{% endset %}
