Example issues artifact when the implementation needs fixes:

```markdown
---
type: issues
status: issues_found
---

## Summary
- [SUM-1] The feature works in the happy path, but error handling and regression coverage are incomplete.

## Issues
- [I-1] ralph/pipeline/runner.py | high | A failure path still treats runtime text as markup.

## What Came Up Short
- [W-1] ralph/pipeline/runner.py still has one failure output path that renders runtime text unsafely.
- [W-2] There is no regression test proving malformed tool output cannot crash the remaining CLI error output path.

## How To Fix
- [F-1] Convert the remaining CLI failure output path to a Rich Text-based render so runtime strings are always treated as literal text.
- [F-2] Add a regression test that feeds bracket-heavy runtime text through the affected path and confirms rendering does not raise MarkupError.
```
